## go terms associated with terms
modules2terms <- c("04977", "04714", "04071", "00600", "04723", "04923", "04722", "04217", 
    "01100", "04931", "00561", "00564", "04975", "04979", "04920")
# keggPath2genes function
keggPath2genes <- function(Organism = "hsa", Path = Path, Output) {
    pathways <- paste0(Organism, Path)
    genes <- c()
    PathwayMap <- c()
    for (i in seq_along(pathways)) {
        pathway <- pathways[i]
        names <- try(keggGet(pathway)[[1]]$GENE, silent = TRUE)
        ## associated pathway
        Pathways <- try(keggGet(pathway)[[1]]$PATHWAY_MAP, silent = TRUE)
        ## unname
        Pathways <- try(unname(Pathways), silent = TRUE)
        # delete the gene number
        namesodd <- try(names[seq(0, length(names), 2)], silent = TRUE)
        ## create substring
        namestrue <- try(gsub("\\;.*", "", namesodd), silent = TRUE)
        ## append
        genes <- try(append(genes, namestrue), silent = TRUE)
        PathwayMap <- try(append(PathwayMap, Pathways), silent = TRUE)
    }
    genes <- unique(genes)
    if (Output == "genes") {
        return(genes)
    } else if (Output == "pathway_map") 
        return(PathwayMap)
}
## extract genes
genes <- keggPath2genes(Organism = "hsa", Path = modules2terms, Output = "genes")

## assign expression
ssgsea <- exprs(gsva)
## subset gsea data for all kegg terms
pathwayMap <- keggPath2genes(Organism = "hsa", Path = modules2terms, Output = "pathway_map")
pathwayMap <- gsub(" ", "_", pathwayMap)
### subset ssgsea by PathwayMap
ssgseaSubset <- ssgsea[grepl(paste0(toupper(c(pathwayMap)), collapse = "|"), rownames(ssgsea)), 
    ]
## define pheatmap clusters
cluster_size <- 3
## basic heatmap
heatmap.px <- pheatmap(ssgseaSubset, scale = "row", kmean_k = cluster_size, cluster_rows = FALSE, 
    cluster_cols = TRUE, silent = TRUE)
## annotation_columns
cluster <- cbind(heatmap.px, cluster = cutree(heatmap.px$tree_col, k = cluster_size))
cluster <- as.data.frame(unlist(cluster[, 2]))
colnames(cluster) <- c("Pseudoclusters")
cluster$Pseudoclusters <- sub("^", "Cluster", cluster$Pseudoclusters)
## add clusters to phenodata
pdac.subtype <- pdac.subtype %>% tibble::column_to_rownames("Tumor Sample ID")
rownames(pdac.subtype) <- gsub("-", ".", rownames(pdac.subtype))
pData <- merge(pdac.subtype, cluster, by = 0, all = TRUE)
## format pData
pData <- pData %>% tibble::column_to_rownames("Row.names")
## column annotations
cluster <- as.data.frame(cbind(cluster = pData$Pseudoclusters, Gender = pData$Gender, 
    KRAS = pData$`KRAS Mutated (1 or 0)`, RPPA = sort(pData$`RPPA Clusters (All 150 Samples)`), 
    lnRNA = sort(pData$`lncRNA Clusters (All 150 Samples)`), miRNA = sort(pData$`miRNA Clusters (All 150 Samples)`), 
    CNV = sort(pData$`Copy Number Clusters (All 150 Samples)`), Methylation = sort(pData$`Methylation Clusters (All 150 Samples)`), 
    Moffitt = sort(pData$`mRNA Moffitt clusters (All 150 Samples) 1basal  2classical`), 
    Collisson = sort(pData$`mRNA Collisson clusters (All 150 Samples) 1classical 2exocrine 3QM`), 
    Bailey = sort(pData$`mRNA Bailey Clusters (All 150 Samples) 1squamous 2immunogenic 3progenitor 4ADEX`), 
    Purity = sort(pData$`Purity Class (high or low)`)))
rownames(cluster) <- rownames(pData)

## annotation colors
cluster.col <- rev(brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$cluster)), "Set1"))
names(cluster.col) <- unique(cluster$cluster)

gender.col <- brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$Gender)), "Paired")
names(gender.col) <- unique(cluster$Gender)

kras.col <- brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$KRAS)), "Set2")
names(kras.col) <- unique(cluster$KRAS)

rppa.col <- brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$RPPA)), "Set3")
names(rppa.col) <- unique(cluster$RPPA)

lnrna.col <- brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$lnRNA)), "Accent")
names(lnrna.col) <- unique(cluster$lnRNA)

mirna.col <- brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$miRNA)), "Pastel1")
names(mirna.col) <- unique(cluster$miRNA)

cnv.col <- brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$CNV)), "Pastel2")
names(cnv.col) <- unique(cluster$CNV)

methyl.col <- brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$Methylation)), "Dark2")
names(methyl.col) <- unique(cluster$Methylation)

moffitt.col <- brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$Moffitt)), "Set1")
names(moffitt.col) <- unique(cluster$Moffitt)

collisson.col <- brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$Collisson)), "Set3")
names(collisson.col) <- unique(cluster$Collisson)

bailey.col <- brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$Bailey)), "Set2")
names(bailey.col) <- unique(cluster$Bailey)

purity.col <- brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$Purity)), "Accent")
names(purity.col) <- unique(cluster$Purity)

## combo color
combo.cols <- list(cluster = cluster.col, Gender = gender.col[1:2], KRAS = kras.col[1:2], 
    RPPA = rppa.col, lnRNA = lnrna.col[1:2], miRNA = mirna.col, CNV = cnv.col, Methylation = methyl.col, 
    Moffitt = moffitt.col[1:2], Collisson = collisson.col, Bailey = bailey.col, Purity = purity.col[1:2])

# color breaks

    cluster_cols = TRUE, show_rownames = TRUE, show_colnames = FALSE, cex = 1, border_color = FALSE, 
    main = "Metabolites distribution", display_numbers = FALSE, cellwidth = 3, cellheight = 10, 
    cutree_cols = 3, annotation_col = cluster, annotation_colors = combo.cols, )

4 Pie chart

pData$Stage <- gsub("_n.*", "", pData$`AJCC pathologic tumor stage`)
pData$Stage <- gsub("stage ", "", pData$Stage)
pData$Stage <- ifelse(grepl("ia", pData$Stage) | grepl("ib", pData$Stage) | grepl("iia", 
    pData$Stage) | grepl("iib", pData$Stage), "Grade 1_2", pData$Stage)
## create data
datPie <- pData %>% group_by(Pseudoclusters, Stage) %>% summarise(Freq = length(Stage)) %>% 
    arrange(Stage) %>% na.omit()
## define groups
class <- unique(datPie$Stage)

for (i in seq_along(class)) {
    ## filtered dataclass[i],]
    filteredData <- datPie[datPie$Stage %in% class[i], ]
    ## samples
    nSamples <- sum(filteredData$Freq)
    ## add percent
    filteredData <- filteredData %>% mutate(prop = percent(Freq/nSamples))
    ## plot
    p <- filteredData %>% ggplot(aes(x = "", y = Freq)) + geom_bar(aes(fill = Pseudoclusters), 
        width = 0.1, stat = "identity", color = "gray50") + coord_polar("y", start = 0) + 
        scale_fill_manual(values = brewer.pal(3, "Set1")) + theme_void() + labs(title = paste(class[i], 
        "n=", nSamples)) + theme(legend.title = element_blank(), legend.position = "bottom", 
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + guides(fill = guide_legend(ncol = 3)) + 
        theme(plot.margin = unit(c(1, 1, 1, 1), "lines")) + geom_label_repel(aes(label = prop), 
        size = 5, show.legend = F, nudge_x = 3)
    ## print
    print(p)
    ## save plot
    save_plot(paste0("../results/nmf/pieChart_tcga_", class[i], ".svg"), fig = p, width = 9, 
        height = 6, dpi = 300)
}

## assign expression
ssgsea <- exprs(gsva)
### subset ssgsea by PathwayMap
ssgseaSubset <- ssgsea[grepl(paste0(toupper(c(pathwayMap)), collapse = "|"), rownames(ssgsea)), 
    ]
## define pheatmap clusters
cluster_size <- 3
## basic heatmap
heatmap.px <- pheatmap(ssgseaSubset, scale = "row", kmean_k = cluster_size, cluster_rows = TRUE, 
    cluster_cols = TRUE, silent = TRUE)
## annotation_columns
cluster <- cbind(heatmap.px, cluster = cutree(heatmap.px$tree_col, k = cluster_size))
cluster <- as.data.frame(unlist(cluster[, 2]))
colnames(cluster) <- c("Pseudoclusters")
cluster$Pseudoclusters <- sub("^", "Cluster", cluster$Pseudoclusters)
## add clusters to phenodata
pData <- merge(pdac.subtype, cluster, by = 0, all = TRUE)
## format pData
pData <- pData %>% tibble::column_to_rownames("Row.names")
## column annotations
cluster <- as.data.frame(cbind(cluster = pData$Pseudoclusters, tumorSubtype = pData$`tumor_subtype_0na_1classical_2basal:ch2`, 
    stromaSubtype = pData$`stroma_subtype_0na_1low_2normal_3activated:ch2`))
rownames(cluster) <- rownames(pData)

## annotation colors
cluster.col <- rev(brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$cluster)), "Set1"))
names(cluster.col) <- unique(cluster$cluster)

tumorSubtype.col <- brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$tumorSubtype)), "Paired")
names(tumorSubtype.col) <- unique(cluster$tumorSubtype)

stromaSubtype.col <- brewer.pal(length(unique(cluster$stromaSubtype)), "Set2")
names(stromaSubtype.col) <- unique(cluster$stromaSubtype)
